==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: orb-weaver
<hw>orb"-weav`er</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>Any spider of the family <fam>Araneidae</fam> (called
also <fam>Argiopidae</fam>) that spins a web with a pattern of lines
spiraling outward from the center. They have eight similar eyes. The
golden orb weaver, <spn>Mephila clavipes</spn>, is known for the
remarkable dragline silk it produces for use as a frame for its web and
as a line on which it can plummet down and nab prey. This silk has a
high tensile strength and is stronger than the toughest current
synthetic polymer (Kevlar).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orby</ent>⟦br⟧
